-- Greek shares down 2 pct after first-round vote
-- By Alistair Smout
-- Thu Dec 18, 2014 06:12AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 18 (Reuters) - Greek stocks extended losses in midday trade Thursday, with the Athens share index <.ATG> down over 2 percent after a first-round presidential vote saw Prime Minister Antonis Samaras lose by a larger-than-expected margin.

A poll after Wednesday's vote showed radical leftist Syriza party holds a 3.6-percentage-point lead over the ruling conservatives. [ID:nL6N0U14SZ]